 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nFor sponsorship reasons, the league was known as the [[Jewson]] Wessex League.<ref name=\"FCHD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fchd.info/lghist/wessex2003.htm |title=2002\u201303 Wessex League |accessdate=24 January 2014 |publisher=FCHD}}</ref>\n\n==League table==\nThe league consisted of one division of 22 clubs, reduced from 23 the previous season, after [[Fleet Town F.C.|Fleet Town]] were promoted to the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]], [[Swanage Town & Herston F.C.|Swanage Town & Herston]] were relegated and one new club joined:<ref name=\"FCHD\" />\n*[[Alton Town F.C.|Alton Town]], joining from the [[Hampshire League]].\n{{fb cl header|sort=y}}\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n|1||align=left|[[Eastleigh F.C.|Eastleigh]] '''(C) (P)'''||42||32||7||3||115||32||+83||103||Joined the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]]\n|-\n|2||align=left|[[Gosport Borough F.C.|Gosport Borough]]||42||27||7||8||94||43||+51||88\n|-\n|3||align=left|[[A.F.C. Totton]]||42||27||6||9||96||47||+49||87\n|-\n|4||align=left|[[Wimborne Town F.C.|Wimborne Town]]||42||26||7||9||113||44||+69||85\n|-\n|5||align=left|[[Fareham Town F.C.|Fareham Town]]||42||22||10||10||78||47||+31||76\n|-\n|6||align=left|[[New Milton Town F.C.|Lymington & New Milton]]||42||22||8||12||89||56||+33||74\n|-\n|7||align=left|[[Andover F.C.|Andover]]||42||22||7||13||95||63||+32||73\n|-\n|8||align=left|[[Portland United F.C.|Portland United]]||42||20||8||14||81||62||+19||68\n|-\n|9||align=left|[[Thatcham Town F.C.|Thatcham Town]]||42||18||13||11||68||58||+10||67\n|-\n|10||align=left|[[Moneyfields F.C.|Moneyfields]]||42||18||6||18||73||68||+5||60\n|-\n|11||align=left|[[Totton & Eling F.C.|B.A.T. Sports]]||42||18||6||18||57||65||\u20138||60\n|-\n|12||align=left|[[A.F.C. Newbury]]||42||17||6||19||77||72||+5||57\n|-\n|13||align=left|[[Christchurch F.C.|Christchurch]]||42||15||10||17||58||68||\u201310||55\n|-\n|14||align=left|[[Bournemouth F.C.|Bournemouth]]||42||15||9||18||57||67||\u201310||54\n